Norway - _Trichinella_ spp. (inf. with)
---------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 10 Aug 2022 [see epidemiological comments]
Confirmed: 18 Aug 2022
Reported: 19 Dec 2022 [Note: published by WOAH on 3 Jan 2023]
Reason for notification: recurrence of an eradicated disease
Last occurrence: 31 Dec 1994
Causal agent: _Trichinella_ spp.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Sveasletta, Isfjorden, Svalbard, Svalbard and Jan Mayen
Started: 10 Aug 2022
Epidemiological unit: other
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Polar bear (wild) / - / 1 / - / 1 / - / -

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the event start date is 10 Aug 22. The polar bear was sampled during a forensic autopsy.

No control measures applied.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Norwegian Veterinary Institute (NVI)
Species / Test / Outbreaks / First result date / Last result date / Result
